    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I think I found the part that issues the slow down, it is the \"templates\" part:\n\n```\nvar table   = Hogan.compile($.trim($('#table-template').text()));\nvar stats   = Hogan.compile($.trim($('#stats-template').text()));\nvar hits    = Hogan.compile($.trim($('#hit-template').text()));\n\nsearch.addWidget(\n    instantsearch.widgets.hits({\n        container: '#table-container',\n        templates: {\n            empty: '<table class=\"table table-bordered table-suchergebnisliste\"><tbody id=\"hits\">No Results</tbody></table>',\n            // Template MUST be a full <table>, see https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/770#issuecomment-184115613\n            allItems:  function(data) {react!\n                var stats_html  = stats.render(data);\n                var hits_html   = '';\n                $.each(data.hits, function(a, b) {\n                    hits_html += hits.render(b);\n                });\n                var table_html  = table.render({stats: stats_html, hits: hits_html});\n\n                return table_html;\n            },\n        },\n        hitsPerPage:    15,\n        transformData:  function(data) {\n            data.processingTimeS = data.processingTimeMS / 100;\n            return data;\n        }\n  })\n);\n```\n\nWhen I disable the whole `template:` part, typing into the search box works as expected, it is rapid fast. It seems that the HTML generation is synchronous. \n",
    "created_at": "2016-03-22T09:01:02Z",
