    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Ok, much better now. But there is still a flickering at the moment when the hash URL is updated the cursor jumps forward and backwards and it seems that chars are lost at that moment. Not sure since I type \"w\"'s all the time. This seems related to the treshold thing. \n\nI tried to make a screen recording but it failed because the fps were not fast enough... \n\n---\n\nI found something. I did tests with this [official Instasearch.js example](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/examples/media/) and Chrome and IE, they both work perfect when I hit and hold a key in the search field. Only my Firefox still had flickering. So **I restarted Firefox with all add-ons deactivated and no more flickering**! It might be that on URL refresh a antivir or addblock plugin/add-ons checks this \"new\" URL and leads to delay?!\n",
